esence of any stellar companion of\nany reasonable mass and age (main sequence, pre main sequence or stripped).\nAlthough this finding is not in direct conflict with model predictions, it does\nrule out what many considered to be the most likely evolutionary scenario for\ntype IIb supernova. (abstract abbreviated)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Oct 2017 19:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Dec 2018 17:54:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-27"}
