uctures (i.e. they cover a small portion of space), it emerges that\n80% of the spectral energy transfer (both in the direct and inverse cascade\ndirections) is localized in about 50% of space, and 50% of the energy transfer\nis localized in only 25% of space.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Nov 2017 11:21:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Mar 2018 19:46:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-28"}
